#Text=The Brooklyn Nets ( 23 - 31 ) defeated the Denver Nuggets ( 20 - 36 ) 110 - 82 on Monday at the Pepsi Center in Denver .
#Text=The Nets dominated this game , finishing with the scoring advantage in every single quarter of play .
#Text=Their shooting percentage was a big reason for that , as they went 47 percent from the field , while the Nuggets finished at just 33 percent .
#Text=The Nets also out - rebounded the Nuggets 57 - 49 , even furthering their advantage and helping them secure an impressive 28 - point victory on the road .
#Text=It was a total team - effort for the Nets on Monday , as they had seven of their ten players reach double figures in points .
#Text=At point guard , Deron Williams did the most for the starters , finishing with 16 points ( 6 - 15 FG , 0 - 2 3Pt , 4 - 4 FT ) and 12 assists in 33 minutes .

#Text=After struggling for a long stretch of the season , it looks as if he may have figured things out during the All-Star break , as he 's posted two double - doubles in a row , a stretch where he 's combined for 28 points and 27 assists .
#Text=Rookie Markel Brown was in the starting lineup and had the best game of his career .
#Text=He set career - highs in both points and rebounds , finishing with 10 and 11 respectively .
#Text=The Nets also saw a huge effort from their bench , with both Brook Lopez and Thaddeus Young doing their part .
#Text=Lopez posted 19 points ( 6 - 17 FG , 0 - 1 3Pt , 7 - 8 FT ) and nine rebounds , while Young had 15 points ( 6 - 11 FG , 1 - 2 3Pt , 2 - 2 FT ) and five rebounds .
#Text=Lopez has put in a couple of strong games in a row , combining for 41 points and 33 rebounds over the last two .
#Text=While most of the Nuggets struggled to get anything going , it was Danilo Gallinari who got hot Monday .
#Text=He went 7 - for - 12 from the field and 3 - for - 5 from the three - point line to score a game - high of 22 points .
#Text=It was his first game shooting over 50 percent from the field since the end of January , so we 'll see if he can keep it up moving forward .
#Text=Coming off the bench , Will Barton had himself a game , recording 15 points ( 5 - 11 FG , 1 - 3 3Pt , 4 - 4 FT ) and four rebounds in just 21 minutes .

#Text=In the two games since coming over from the Trail Blazers , he 's now set a new season - high in points during both outings , as he 's getting a lot more run on the court with the Nuggets than he was with his previous team .
#Text=With Wilson Chandler sitting out , Darrell Arthur moved into the starting lineup and posted 10 points ( 5 - 15 FG ) and seven rebounds .
#Text=It was only his second start of the year , so it was good to see him have some success .
#Text=Rookie Gary Harris was the only other Nugget in double figures , as he finished with 10 points ( 4 - 12 FG , 1 - 6 3Pt , 1 - 3 FT ) of his own .
#Text=The Nets ' next game will be on the road against the New Orleans Pelicans on Wednesday , while the Nuggets will be at home against the Phoenix Suns on Wednesday .
